{"title_page": "Nakodar (Rural)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2019}}\n\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = Nakodar (Rural)\n| official_name                   = \n| native_name                     = \n| native_name_lang                = \n| settlement_type                 = Village\n| pushpin_map                     = India Punjab#India\n| pushpin_label_position          = \n| pushpin_map_alt                 = \n| pushpin_map_caption             = Location in Punjab, India\n| coordinates                     = {{coord|31.1316524|N|75.4543591|E|display=inline,title|format=dms}}\n| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = [[India]]\n| subdivision_type1               = [[States and territories of India|State]]\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Punjab, India|Punjab]]\n| subdivision_type2               = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Jalandhar district|Jalandhar]]\n| subdivision_type3               = Tehsil\n| subdivision_name3               = [[Nakodar]]\n| subdivision_type4               = Region\n| subdivision_name4               = \n| government_type                 = [[Panchayati raj (India)|Panchayat raj]]\n| governing_body                  = [[Gram panchayat]]\n| unit_pref                       = Metric\n<!-- ALL fields with measurements have automatic unit conversion -->\n<!-- for references: use <ref>tags -->| elevation_m                     = \n| population_as_of                = 2011\n| population_blank2_title         = Total Households\n| population_blank2               = 88\n| population_total                = 481<br/><small>236/245 [[male|\u2642]]/[[female|\u2640]]</small>\n| population_density_km2          = 23\n| population_note                 = \n| population_blank1_title         = Scheduled Castes\n| population_blank1               = 352<br/><small>174/178 [[male|\u2642]]/[[female|\u2640]]</small>\n| population_demonym              = \n| demographics_type1              = Languages\n| demographics1_title1            = Official\n| demographics1_info1             = [[Punjabi language|Punjabi]]\n| demographics1_title2            = \n| demographics1_info2             = \n| timezone1                       = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1                     = +5:30\n| postal_code_type                = \n| postal_code                     = \n| area_total_ha                   = 2080\n| area_code_type                  = Telephone\n| area_code                       = 01821\n| registration_plate              = \n| iso_code                        = IN-PB\n| blank1_name_sec2                = \n| blank1_info_sec2                = \n| website                         = {{URL|Jalandhar.gov.in}}\n| footnotes                       = \n}}\n'''Nakodar''' (Rural) is a village in [[Nakodar]] in [[Jalandhar district]] of [[Punjab, India|Punjab]] [[States and territories of India|State]], India. It is located {{convert|2|km}} from sub district headquarter and {{convert|26|km}} from district headquarter. The village is [[Administration (government)|administrated]] by [[Sarpanch]] an elected representative of the village. Nakodar (Rural) is unique among surrounding villages as the geographical area of this village being {{convert|2080|ha|km2}}, is very large for a scattered population of only 481 people. In contrast the adjoining [[Nakodar]] town area is {{convert|1250|ha|km2}}.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://censusindia.gov.in/2011census/dchb/0303_PART_B_DCHB_JALANDHAR.pdf|title=District Census Handbook  Jalandhar - Village and Town Wise Primary Census Abstract (Pca)|website=[[2011 Census of India|Census of India]]|access-date=29 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Demography ==\n{{as of|2011}}, The village has a total number of 88 houses and the population of 481 of which 236 are males while 245 are females.<ref name=census>{{cite web|url=http://www.censusindia.gov.in/2011census/dchb/DCHB_Village_Release_0300.xlsx|title=DCHB Village Release|work=[[Census of India, 2011]]}}</ref>  According to the report [[published]] by [[Census India]] in 2011, out of the total population of the village 352 people are from [[Scheduled Castes and Scheduled Tribes|Schedule Caste]] and the village does not have any [[Scheduled Castes and Scheduled Tribes|Schedule Tribe]] population so far.<ref name=census /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://censusindia.gov.in/pca/SearchDetails.aspx?Id=32762|title=Census Data of Nakodar (Rural) village|website=Office of the Registrar General & Census Commissioner, India|access-date=29 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of villages in India]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.punjabtourism.gov.in/ Tourism of Punjab]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20180804201629/http://punjabcensus.gov.in/ Census of Punjab]\n\n{{Jalandhar district}}\n\n[[Category:Villages in Jalandhar district]]\n\n\n{{Jalandhar-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2019}}\n\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = Nakodar (Rural)\n| official_name                   = \n| native_name                     = \n| native_name_lang                = \n| settlement_type                 = Village\n| pushpin_map                     = India Punjab#India\n| pushpin_label_position          = \n| pushpin_map_alt                 = \n| pushpin_map_caption             = Location in Punjab, India\n| coordinates                     = {{coord|31.1316524|N|75.4543591|E|display=inline,title|format=dms}}\n| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = [[India]]\n| subdivision_type1               = [[States and territories of India|State]]\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Punjab, India|Punjab]]\n| subdivision_type2               = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Jalandhar di