4 new COVID-19 cases, bringing the total to 101.\n\n====March 20====\nAs of March 20, the U.S had 19,285 confirmed cases of COVID-19 resulting in 249 deaths.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/health/2020/03/20/coronavirus-updates-us-deaths-cases-stay-home-order-trump/2880695001/|title=Coronavirus updates: U.S. infections approach 20,000; NY, Illinois unleash strict rules; 150 Detroit cops quarantined|first1=Ryan|last1=Miller|first2=Marco|last2=Cava|date=March 20, 2020|website=usatoday.com|access-date=March 21, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321020308/https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/health/2020/03/20/coronavirus-updates-us-deaths-cases-stay-home-order-trump/2880695001/|archive-date=March 21, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n*California: Los Angeles Mayor [[Eric Garcetti]] promised that no one will go to jail for violating the [[stay-at-home order]] that goes into effect at midnight. However, a major purpose of the order is to provide enforcement for businesses which are not complying.<ref>\"[https://deadline.com/2020/03/los-angeles-mayor-shutdown-enforcement-order-eric-garcetti-lapd-1202888219/ L.A. Mayor Promises 'People Aren't Going To Be Marched Into Jail' Under New Safer At Home Order] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320200928/https://deadline.com/2020/03/los-angeles-mayor-shutdown-enforcement-order-eric-garcetti-lapd-1202888219/ |date=March 20, 2020 }}\" by Dominic Patten, ''Deadline'', March 20, 2020</ref> Marijuana dispensaries are classified \"essential\".<ref>[https://edition.cnn.com/2020/03/20/us/la-marijuana-coronavirus-trnd/index.html Marijuana dispensaries are deemed 'essential' in LA, allowed to stay open during coronavirus order] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321025617/https://edition.cnn.com/2020/03/20/us/la-marijuana-coronavirus-trnd/index.html |date=March 21, 2020 }} By Allen Kim, CNN, 20 Mar 2020</ref>\n*Illinois: Governor [[J.B. Pritzker]] issued a stay-at-home order.