ivil-emergency-after-maine-announces-new-coronavirus-cases/ |archive-date=March 17, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* Minnesota: Governor Tim Walz closed all schools from March 18 until at least March 27. The state confirmed that there were now 35 confirmed cases of the virus with at least three spread person to person in the state. During the school shutdown meals and mental health services will still be provided to students in need.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.startribune.com/minnesota-schools-will-close-for-eight-days-due-to-coronavirus-pandemic/568812082/?refresh=true |title=Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz closing K-12 schools as COVID-19 spreads |access-date=March 16, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319210909/http://www.startribune.com/minnesota-schools-will-close-for-eight-days-due-to-coronavirus-pandemic/568812082/?refresh=true |archive-date=March 19, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Under the governor's order, schools will remain open for the elementary-aged children of health care workers and other emergency workers.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fox9.com/news/walz-schools-to-remain-open-for-children-of-health-care-workers-emergency-responders |title=Walz: Schools to remain open for children of health care workers, emergency responders |date=2020-03-15 |access-date=March 16, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319210907/https://www.fox9.com/news/walz-schools-to-remain-open-for-children-of-health-care-workers-emergency-responders |archive-date=March 19, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Teachers will be using this time to plan for a possibility of weeks of long-distance learning.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mprnews.org/story/2020/03/14/walz-minnesota-schools-closed-covid19 |title=Walz announces temporary closure of Minnesota K-12 public schools |access-date=March 16, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200316125656/https://www.mprnews.org/story/2020/03/14/walz-minnesota-schools-closed-covid19 |archive-date=March 16, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* New Hampshire: Governor Christopher Sununu orders all public K-12 schools to transition to remote learning effective Monday, March 16 through April 3, 2020, requiring remote learning to begin by March 23, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.governor.nh.gov/news-media/emergency-orders/documents/emergency-order-1.pdf|title=Emergency Order 1 - Temporary remote instruction and support for public K-12 school districts|last=Sununu|first=Christopher|date=March 15, 2020|website=State of New Hampshire, Office of the Governor|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n*North Carolina: [[Mecklenburg County, North Carolina|Mecklenburg]] County which encompassed the city of Charlotte declared a state of emergency in the county after 2 more new cases are found in the county, bringing the total in the county to 4 and the total statewide to 33.<ref name=\":11a\">{{cite web |url=https://www.charlotteobserver.com/news/local/article241209266.html |title=Mecklenburg declares state of emergency over coronavirus; city plans no-contact meetings |last=Smoot |first=Hannah |date=15 March 2020 |website=Charlotte Observer |url-status=live |access-date=16 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317054322/https://www.charlotteobserver.com/news/local/article241209266.html |archive-date=March 17, 2020 }}</ref>\n* North Dakota: Governor Burgum ordered all schools to be closed from March 16 to March 20. It was confirmed the state lab had tested 112 individuals for the virus with one case coming back positive from a person with travel history.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.governor.nd.gov/news/burgum-orders-k-12-schools-close-one-week-effort-slow-spread-covid-19 |title=Burgum orders K-12 schools to close for one week in effort to slow spread of COVID-19 |date=March 15, 2020 |website=North Dakota Office of the Governor |language=en |access-date=March 18, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318065016/https://www.