ia: Governor Northam announces a ban on gatherings of more than 10 people. 15 new cases are reported, bringing the total to 67 cases in Virginia.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.wsls.com/news/virginia/2020/03/17/15-new-coronavirus-cases-in-virginia-now-67-total-cases/ |title=15 new coronavirus cases in Virginia, now 67 total cases |last=Williamson |first=Jeff |date=2020-03-17 |website=WSLS |language=en |access-date=2020-03-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318041135/https://www.wsls.com/news/virginia/2020/03/17/15-new-coronavirus-cases-in-virginia-now-67-total-cases/ |archive-date=March 18, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> \n*[[West Virginia]]: Confirmed its first case; it was the last US state to do so.<ref name=\"Mar17_WV\">{{Cite news |url=https://myfox8.com/news/coronavirus/west-virginia-the-last-us-state-without-coronavirus-confirms-1st-case/ |title=West Virginia, the last US state without coronavirus, confirms 1st case |access-date=March 17, 2020 |agency=Associated Press |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317224314/https://myfox8.com/news/coronavirus/west-virginia-the-last-us-state-without-coronavirus-confirms-1st-case/ |archive-date=March 17, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nAs of March 17, vessel manifests maintained by [[U.S. Customs and Border Protection]] showed a steady flow of the medical equipment needed to treat the coronavirus being shipped abroad. [[FEMA]], meanwhile, said the agency \"has not actively encouraged or discouraged U.S. companies from exporting overseas\", and has asked USAID to send back its reserves of protective gear stored in warehouses for use in the U.S.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.politico.com/news/2020/03/31/pence-task-force-coronavirus-aid-157806|title=Pence task force freezes coronavirus aid amid backlash|website=Politico}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://theintercept.com/2020/04/01/coronavirus-medical-supplies-export |title=Key Medical Supplies Exported From U.S. to Foreign Buyers |publisher=Theintercept.com |date=2020-04-01 |accessdate=2020-04-07}}</ref>\n\nPresident Trump stated to reporters: \"This is a pandemic...I felt it was a pandemic long before it was called a pandemic.\"<ref name=\"NPR_WHO1\"/>\n\n==== March 18 ====\n* Florida: U.S. congressman [[Mario D\u00edaz-Balart]] is one of the first members of Congress to be tested positive for coronavirus.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/18/politics/mario-diaz-balart-coronavirus/index.html|title=Reps. Mario Diaz-Balart and Ben McAdams become first members of Congress to test positive for coronavirus|first=Paul|last=Leblanc|date=March 18, 2020|website=cnn.com|access-date=March 21, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321105409/https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/18/politics/mario-diaz-balart-coronavirus/index.html|archive-date=March 21, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Thousands of spring-breakers flock to Florida beaches despite warnings about keeping social distance. The [[Clearwater, Florida|Clearwater City Council]] voted to close down [[Clearwater Beach]] for two weeks, starting March 23 at 6 a.m. The coronavirus has infected 328 Florida residents and visitors.<ref>[https://news.yahoo.com/thousands-flock-florida-beaches-ignoring-060744453.html Thousands flock to Florida beaches, ignoring coronavirus concerns] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320221138/https://news.yahoo.com/thousands-flock-florida-beaches-ignoring-060744453.html |date=March 20, 2020 }} by Sophie Lewis, CBS New, 18 Mar 2020</ref>\n*Kentucky: The wife of [[List of mayors of Louisville, Kentucky|Louisville mayor]] [[Greg Fischer]] tested positive for coronavirus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.courier-journal.com/story/news/politics/metro-government/2020/03/18/louisville-mayor-greg-fischers-wife-tests-positive-covid-19/2869369001/|title=Louisville Mayor Greg Fischer's wife tests positive for coronavirus, will self-isolate|first=Darcy|last=Costello|website=The Courier-Journal|accessdate=Mar 19, 2020}}</ref>\n*Louisiana: Rev. Tony Spell of Life Tabernacle Church in [[East Baton Rouge Parish]] hosts hundreds at a church service in open defiance of Governor [[John Bel Edwards|John Bel Edwards']] (D) ban against gatherings of more than 50 people.<ref>[https://thehill.com/policy/healthcare/488318-louisiana-church-defies-coronavirus-recommendations-to-hold-service-for-300?fbclid=IwAR3Fy0WDhtRR-_dCFyYFj1nXwqMw1aeImfznyKF5NlxAGjGEZSsIeQjcYXo Louisiana church defies coronavirus recommendations to hold service for 300] BY ZACK BUDRYK, The Hill, 18 Mar 2020</ref>\n* Maryland: The state added 22 more coronavirus cases, to the total of 63 cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/maryland-virginia-dc-coronavirus-tuesday-updates/2020/03/17/5f6fa73c-684e-11ea-9923-57073adce27c_story.html|title=Coronavirus cases surge as Northam bans gatherings of more than 10, Hogan postpones primary|last=Chason|first=Rachel|date=18 March 2020|website=Washington Post|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318121502/https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/maryland-virginia-dc-coronavirus-tuesday-updates/2020/03/17/5f6fa73c-684e-11ea-9923-57073adce27c_story.html|archive-date=March 18, 2020|access-date=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n*Michigan: The first death from coronavirus in the state is reported, a man in his 50s who had underlying medical conditions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/news/local/2020/03/18/man-at-wayne-county-hospital-is-michigans-first-confirmed-coronavirus-death/|title=Man at Wayne County hospital is Michigan's first confirmed coronavirus death|website=clickondetroit.com|accessdate=18 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318231056/https://www.clickondetroit.com/news/local/2020/03/18/man-at-wayne-county-hospital-is-michigans-first-confirmed-coronavirus-death/|archive-date=March 18, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The state also announces 30 more confirmed cases, bringing the total number there to 110.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/news/local/2020/03/18/michigan-officials-state-has-at-least-30-more-confirmed-cases-of-coronavirus-covid-19-bringing-total-to-110/|title=Michigan officials: State has at least 30 more confirmed cases of coronavirus (COVID-19), bringing total to 110|website=clickondetroit.com|accessdate=18 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318231055/https://www.clickondetroit.com/news/local/2020/03/18/michigan-officials-state-has-at-least-30-more-confirmed-cases-of-coronavirus-covid-19-bringing-total-to-110/|archive-date=March 18, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*Minnesota: Governor Tim Walz criticized the federal response to the virus. The state had approximately 1700 frozen samples to be tested, but had not yet been, due to the lack of facilities for testing. The state had 77 positive results out of at least 2762 tests.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fox10phoenix.com/news/minnesota-has-1700-frozen-samples-waiting-on-coronavirus-testing-but-tests-are-in-short-supply|title=Minnesota has 1,700 frozen samples waiting on coronavirus testing but tests are in short supply|accessdate= March 24, 2020}}</ref>\n*Montana: Governor [[Steve Bullock (American politician)|Steve Bullock]] announces 2 additional cases in Gallatin county, bringing the confirmed total to 12 in Montana.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ktvq.com/news/coronavirus/bullock-confirms-two-more-montana-covid-19-cases|title=Bullock confirms two more cases Montana COVID-19 cases|date=2020-03-18|website=ktvq.com|accessdate=18 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319041512/https://www.ktvq.com/news/coronavirus/bullock-confirms-two-more-montana-covid-19-cases|archive-date=March 19, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*North Carolina: The number of cases in the state jumped to 81.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://myfox8.com/news/coronavirus/number-of-coronavirus-cases-in-north-carolina-jumps-to-81-u-s-number-tops-7000/|title=Number of coronavirus cases in North Carolina jumps to 81; U.S. number tops 7,000|date=2020-03-18|website=myfox8.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319015545/https://myfox8.com/news/coronavirus/number-of-coronavirus-cases-in-north-carolina-jumps-to-81-u-s-number-tops-7000/|archive-date=March 19, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* Ohio: The state has 88 confirmed cases across 19 counties. 26 cases involved hospitalization.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.10tv.com/article/ohio-confirms-first-coronavirus-cases-continues-testing-2020-mar|title=88 confirmed cases of coronavirus in Ohio; 26 hospitalized|date=March 18, 2020|website=10tv.com|access-date=March 18, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318055740/https://www.10tv.com/article/ohio-confirms-first-coronavirus-cases-continues-testing-2020-mar|archive-date=March 18, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Governor Mike DeWine announces 181 Divisions of Motor Vehicle locations will close until further notice. Five will stay open to process commercial driver license applications and renewals. DeWine asks state legislatures to allow a grace period for people whose licenses have expired. Barbershops, salons, and tattoo parlors are closed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbc4i.com/community/health/coronavirus/coronavirus-in-ohio-wednesday-update-from-governor-odh-set-for-for-2-p-m/|title=Coronavirus in Ohio Wednesday update: 88 cases of COVID-19 confirmed|date=March 18, 2020|website=nbc4i.com|access-date=March 18, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318211617/https://www.nbc4i.com/community/health/coronavirus/coronavirus-in-ohio-wednesday-update-from-governor-odh-set-for-for-2-p-m/|archive-date=March 18, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Businesses that do stay open are asked to take their employees' temperatures every day before allowing them entry to work and to send sick employees home.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbc4i.com/community/health/coronavirus/dewine-businesses-should-take-employees-temperatures-