g despite not having any cases of Covid-19 on board.<ref>[https://news.yahoo.com/two-cruise-ships-turned-away-145857760.html Despite no reported coronavirus, Hawaii won't let cruise ship passengers disembark] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320214212/https://news.yahoo.com/two-cruise-ships-turned-away-145857760.html |date=March 20, 2020 }} by CHRISTINA CARREGA, ABC News, 19 Mar 2020</ref>\n*Massachusetts: The [[Massachusetts Medical Society]] says there is a \"dire\" shortage of protective medical equipment in the state.<ref>[https://www.rawstory.com/2020/03/dire-shortage-of-personal-protective-equipment-reported-in-massachusetts-reports/?fbclid=IwAR2hhQhjCTatrh7HLPS8eBg9lX9RKLcZ9Yodtkqiwjrf83vCy6d9SD9ALMA \u2018Dire\u2019 shortage of personal protective equipment reported in Massachusetts: reports] By Matthew Chapman, Raw Story, 19 Mar 2020</ref>\n* Michigan: The state reports two additional coronavirus deaths.<ref>{{cite web |title=3 confirmed coronavirus deaths in Michigan: What we know about the patients |url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/news/local/2020/03/19/3-confirmed-coronavirus-deaths-in-michigan-what-we-know-about-the-patients/ |website=clickondetroit.com |accessdate=20 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320021027/https://www.clickondetroit.com/news/local/2020/03/19/3-confirmed-coronavirus-deaths-in-michigan-what-we-know-about-the-patients/ |archive-date=March 20, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Meanwhile, the total number of cases in the state rises to 334, an increase of 254 from the previous day. Officials attribute the spike to an increase in testing.<ref>{{cite web |title=Michigan coronavirus (COVID-19) cases spike to 334 as testing ramps up |url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/health/2020/03/19/michigan-coronavirus-covid-19-cases-spike-to-336-as-testing-ramps-up/ |website=clickondetroit.com |accessdate=20 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320021026/https://www.clickondetroit.com/health/20